{
  "texts": [
    "Acronyms: PKT (PheKnowLator).",
    "A UUID is a blank or anonymous node that is created from an md5 hash of concatenated Universal Resource Identifiers (URIs).",
    "The URIs used in the hash string include the subject and object URIs (each appended with \"subject\" and \"object, \" respectively) in addition to a relation.",
    "All UUIDs created during construction are explicitly defined within the PKT namespace (https://github.com/callahantiff/PheKnowLator/pkt/).",
    "FAIR data principles."
  ]
}